resource.http://dev.llgc.org.uk/sas/full_text:
It's pretty rare to represent naked characters in high medieval christian manuscripts.
Maybe they are Adam and Eve, for few reasons. First, they're used to be depicted as naked way more than any other biblical figures. We can only see a penis on the left character, meaning that the right one may have none, leaving the hypothesis that it can be a woman. Therefore, the right character has a long red scar over the belly, maybe representing that Eve comes from Adam's ribs. Last but not least, the scary figure between them would then be the snake manipulating them at the Garden of Eden.
